<emphasis id="B92D8F002371605AD4CCFACEFB43A009" bold="true" box="[746,1156,1332,1356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">
5. A vicariant pair in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5928912371605AD5FDFACEFB43A009" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Balkwill &amp; Balkwill" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[987,1156,1332,1356]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Fissimura">
sect. 
<emphasis id="B92D8F002371605AD235FACEFB43A009" bold="true" box="[1043,1156,1332,1356]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">Fissimura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34300992371605AD2ACFACEFC3DA3D5" pageId="9" pageNumber="91" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE653122371605AD2ACFACEFC3DA3D5" blockId="9.[746,1396,1332,1952]" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">
– Our novelty 
<emphasis id="B92D8F002371605AD303FACFFC8EA02C" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName id="4C5928912371605AD303FACFFCF7A02C" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pauciflora">B. pauciflora</taxonomicName>
is
</emphasis>
similar and closely related to 
<emphasis id="B92D8F002371605AD2AAFAABFAAAA02C" box="[1164,1389,1361,1385]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName id="4C5928912371605AD2AAFAABFB21A02C" baseAuthorityName="Balkwill &amp; Balkwill" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[1164,1254,1361,1385]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Barleria</taxonomicName>
neurophylla
</emphasis>
, a species described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC82EE32371605AD5FAFA95FBB7A0C2" author="Clarke C. B." box="[988,1136,1391,1415]" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Tropical Africa" pageId="9" pageNumber="91" pagination="1 - 262" part="5" refId="ref9289" refString="Clarke C. B. (1900) Acanthaceae. Flora of Tropical Africa 5: 1 - 262." title="Acanthaceae" type="journal article" year="1900">Clarke (1900)</bibRefCitation>
from D.R.Congo. There is no isotype nor any identified material of that species in BR where it has hitherto been overlooked as being a species from Central Africa. The holotype (
<emphasis id="B92D8F002371605AD25FFA3DFB0FA09B" box="[1145,1224,1479,1502]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">Carson</emphasis>
s.n., K) comes from Kavala Island, in the Congolese part of Tanganyika Lake. There is a second Congolese collection from the western shore of the lake, 
<emphasis id="B92D8F002371605AD5C7F9DAFBFFA372" box="[993,1080,1568,1591]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">Kässner</emphasis>
3048 (K). 
<emphasis id="B92D8F002371605AD291F9DAFA9FA372" box="[1207,1368,1567,1591]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">B. neurophylla</emphasis>
is endemic from that part of the lake and from the next Mahali mountains, a small range fringing the eastern shore of the lake in Tanzania (fig. 11).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C343009923716059D536F96CFDF6A3C6" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="92" pageId="9" pageNumber="91" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE653122371605AD536F96CFBFAA218" blockId="9.[746,1396,1332,1952]" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis id="B92D8F002371605AD536F96CFC6AA3E8" box="[784,941,1685,1709]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">B. neurophylla</emphasis>
is very closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5928912371605AD29AF96CFA80A3E8" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[1212,1351,1685,1709]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pauciflora">
<emphasis id="B92D8F002371605AD29AF96CFA80A3E8" box="[1212,1351,1685,1709]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">B. pauciflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and has the same ecology, also growing in gallery forests, but several minor differences in characters and the disjunct distribution of the two taxa justify their treatment as distinct species. They may be considered as vicariant taxa. Several specimens of 
<emphasis id="B92D8F002371605AD521F8D3FC5FA205" box="[775,920,1832,1856]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">B. neurophyll</emphasis>
a were found in K and a duplicate from K in the unidentified material of BR.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE6531223716059D536F890FDF6A3C6" blockId="9.[746,1396,1332,1952]" lastBlockId="10.[56,705,1610,1667]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="92" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">
As 
<emphasis id="B92D8F002371605AD51AF891FC26A2C7" box="[828,993,1898,1922]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">B. neurophylla</emphasis>
is placed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC82EE32371605AD2ADF890FCF6A2E5" pageId="9" pageNumber="91" refId="ref9206" refString="Balkwill M. - J., Balkwill K. (1997) Delimitation and infrageneric classification of Barleria (Acanthaceae). Kew Bulletin 52: 535 - 573. [available at http: // www. jstor. org / pss / 4110286]" type="journal article">Balkwill &amp; Balkwill (1997)</bibRefCitation>
in sect. Fissimura, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5928912371605AD231F873FB6EA2E5" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[1047,1193,1928,1952]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pauciflora">
<emphasis id="B92D8F002371605AD231F873FB6EA2E5" box="[1047,1193,1928,1952]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="91">B. pauciflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be placed there as well. It is an unarmed plant, with bracteoles never spinous, and a corolla with 4 + 1 configuration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
